## Summary

I have successfully implemented the fix for the JacksonDatabind-79 issue. Here's what was accomplished:

### Problem Analysis
The issue was that `@JsonIdentityReference(alwaysAsId=true)` annotation placed on a class definition itself was not being recognized to serialize all usages of that class as IDs by default. The original implementation only checked for `@JsonIdentityReference` on the same annotated element (field/property) but didn't consider when the annotation was placed on the target class type itself.

### Solution Implemented
I modified the `findObjectReferenceInfo` method in `JacksonAnnotationIntrospector.java` to:

1. First, check for `@JsonIdentityReference` on the annotated element itself (preserving existing behavior)
2. If no identity reference was found on the element itself and the `alwaysAsId` property is not already true, then check if the raw type of the annotated member has the `@JsonIdentityReference` annotation on its class definition
3. If the class type has the annotation, apply its `alwaysAsId` setting to the `ObjectIdInfo`

### Code Changes
The fix adds a check in the `findObjectReferenceInfo` method to look for `@JsonIdentityReference` annotation on the class type itself, not just on the field/property where it's used:

```java
// Also check if the type of the annotated member has @JsonIdentityReference
// This handles the case where the annotation is on the class definition itself
if (objectIdInfo != null && !objectIdInfo.getAlwaysAsId()) {
    // Get the type of the annotated member (field type, method return type, etc.)
    Class<?> type = ann.getRawType();
    if (type != null) {
        JsonIdentityReference typeRef = type.getAnnotation(JsonIdentityReference.class);
        if (typeRef != null) {
            objectIdInfo = objectIdInfo.withAlwaysAsId(typeRef.alwaysAsId());
        }
    }
}
```

### Verification
- The fix was tested using the defects4j framework
- All tests now pass, confirming that the fix resolves the issue
- The generated patch file only contains changes to `JacksonAnnotationIntrospector.java` and does not modify `pom.xml` or `build.xml`

This fix ensures that when a class is annotated with `@JsonIdentityReference(alwaysAsId=true)`, all usages of that class throughout the object graph will be serialized as IDs by default, as required by the specification.

